@page "/projects/homelab"
<h1>Homelab</h1>
<p>
    My most recent project has been my home lab. It currently consists of one server and one network switch,
    connecting various parts of the home network. I have been using it to experiment with hypervisors,
    virtualization, docker, nginx, and more. I am even using it to host this site!
</p>

<h2>Server hardware</h2>
<p>
    I am using a Dell PowerEdge R630 server with idrac 8. I recently upgraded the ram from 16GB to 256GB so 
    that it can better run my workload with headroom to configure caching. I currently have two of eight
    2.5" drive bays filled, one acting as the boot drive and storage for virtual machines, the other as a
    storage pool for my TrueNas installation. It has a 4 port 1GB nic to connect to the rest of the network 
    with.
</p>

<h2>Technologies and services</h2>
<p>
    The server is running Proxmox on bare metal, which is currently host to four VMs and three containers.
    I am running Ubuntu server as my docker host, which is currently hosting Nginx, my Minecraft server, 
    and this site. I have Nginx set up to proxy this site and my Jellyfin instance to simplify my cloudflare
    setup. I was previously running OPNsense and pihole, but since I moved and switched networks, I removed
    OPNsense, and pihole is currently disabled.
</p>

